# BioCompiler Hazard Reference Sequences
# ========================================
# Short representative protein fragments (50-100 aa) from conserved regions
# of critical hazard proteins. These are publicly available reference
# sequences from NCBI GenBank (not novel sequences).
#
# These fragments are used to build BLAST+ databases for homology-based
# biosecurity screening. They contain conserved functional motifs sufficient
# for BLAST detection without being full-length toxins.
#
# References:
#   - Lord et al., Toxicon 2003; ricin A-chain
#   - Lacy & Stevens, Nat Struct Biol 1999; botulinum neurotoxin
#   - Pannifer et al., Nature 2001; anthrax lethal factor
#   - Fraser et al., J Biol Chem 1994; shiga toxin
#   - CDC Select Agent Program (42 CFR Part 73)
#   - Australia Group Common Control List
#
# WARNING: These sequences are for biosecurity screening purposes only.
# They must NOT be used to construct functional toxins.

